<TITLE> Actor, director Nantu dies </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 1 (bdnews24.com) -- Film actor and director Siddique Zaman Nantu died Saturday at a Dhaka hospital following a heart attack. He was 60. Freedom fighter Nantu was famous for his role in the Liberation War film 'Ora Egaro Jon', among others. Shah Alam Kiran, leader of Bangabandhu Sangskritik Jote of which Nantu was a leading member, told bdnews24.com: "Nantu died early Saturday at United Hospital." Family, friends and colleagues in the film industry thronged to the hospital after hearing the news of his death. Nantu left behind his wife, two sons and many well wishers. The actor was buried at Mirpur Martyred Intellectuals' Graveyard after two namaz-e-janazas. The first janaza was held at Baridhara and the second at Film Development Corporation in Tejgaon. He was later buried after receiving state honours. Members of BSJ expressed condolences to the bereaved family. bdnew
